      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Higher wages do create a short-term boost in local spending, but this benefit often evaporates quickly when businesses raise prices or cut hours to cover costs. In rural areas with already fragile economies, the immediate risk of small shops closing due to these hikes usually outweighs the long-term economic gains. Instead of relying on government mandates that threaten business survival, your town would be better served by supporting local entrepreneurs with tax incentives or grants to help them thrive without raising prices.",
