    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the risk, but it feels like you're kinda dismissing the human side of it. if workers can't afford basic stuff even with a \"debilitating\" wage hike, isn't that a pretty big failure for the community? wouldn't you say it's unfair to put the whole burden of social dignity on a single small business owner?",
