      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right that placing the entire burden of social dignity on a single small business owner is fundamentally unfair and unsustainable. The human cost of these mandates often leads to business closures that leave the very workers they were supposed to help without jobs, creating a net loss for the community. Instead of forcing small businesses to absorb these costs, the solution lies in targeted government support programs that help rural entrepreneurs survive without sacrificing the dignity of their employees.",
